# Refactoring & File Organization

- All refactoring must include a file organization audit.
- Any moved, renamed, or deleted files must be reflected in the directory structure and documentation.
- Refactoring PRs must not introduce root-level clutter or misplaced files.
- File organization must be checked before merging any refactor.
